&gt;&gt;Yes, many ancestral blades were remounted in gunto koshirae and
&gt;&gt;carried off to the Pacific War. But they were not stamped with the
&gt;&gt;Showa cherry blossom. A Showa stamp, also the nearly as common Seki
&gt;&gt;stamp, indicates the blade is not completely traditionally made. In
&gt;&gt;some better examples that look very traditional, displaying both hada
